Timișoara is the capital city of Timiș County in western Romania. With a population of over 319,000 as of 2011, it is the third most populous city in the country and serves as the main social, economic, and cultural center of the historical region of Banat. Timișoara has held the unofficial title of "Little Vienna" due to its architecture and cultural influences from the Austro-Hungarian Empire during the time it was under Habsburg rule.
